<p>GDP growth: 3.2%  GDP: $542bn (PPP: $805bn)  Inflation: 3.0%  Population: 38.1m GDP per head: $14,250 (PPP: $21,140)</p>

<p>The Civic Platform party cruised to victory in Poland's general election in October, and will re-form its old -coalition with the agrarian Polish Peasants' Party. This will be the first time a Polish prime minister—Donald Tusk—has led two consecutive governments since the fall of communism. Enthusiasm for euro adoption has waned, and the issue will be shuffled to the bottom of the policy deck. Strong domestic consumption will drive growth, and inflation will fall back to a more acceptable level. </p>

